  "body": "The local node alias (private key), nodes, and peers MUST be saved and restored between sessions (network state file/database). The identifier can be reset by deleting network state file/database. An option to reset identifier from UI or CLI is NOT recommended.\n\nDependencies:\n- kademlia: availability is inverse to malice\n- peer reputation\n- peer connection strategy\n\nEffects:\n- reduces network churn\n- reduces convergence overhead from major network events (splits)\n- [future] reduced convergence overhead for DHT\n- tofu: trust on first-use\n",
